line_2: Yet by Pride, by Shame with-held,

line_1: His youthful arm had many a foe repelled,
line_2: Far less a ponderous lance, or sword to wield;

line_1: The captives eyes alone its force repell'd,
line_2: Nor to the pleasing violence would yield.

line_1: When first thou saw'st thy Bravest Troops repell'd,
line_2: That with mixt Tumult in thy Bosom swell'd!
You bid gold-leaves, in crystal lantherns held,

line_1: And to his course the bellowing Fiend repell'd.
line_2: With waving arm the billowy tumult quell'd,

line_1: Minds combat minds, repelling and repell'd;
line_2: Here by the bonds of nature feebly held,
The Hero from the Height beheld:

line_1: Sav'd Europe, in the Blow repell'd:
line_2: Behind, That Angel shall be plac'd, whose Shield

line_1: Where thorny Brakes the Traveller repell'd,
line_2: And Weeds and Thistles overspread the Field;

line_1: But proudly he my Lover's Suit repell'd;
line_2: And, frowning, thus our mutual Ruin seal'd:
